From 7267bdaa9ca2aba371aed837839ca9bd99cf6000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balasubramanian Narasimhan <b.naras@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 16:12:53 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 6/9] Replace direct stdio/abort calls with R API equivalents
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace printf/puts/putchar/vprintf with Rprintf/Rvprintf,
fprintf(stdout/stderr,...) with Rprintf/REprintf, stdout/stderr FILE*
args with NULL, and abort() with Rf_error() across all compiled sources.

Declarations come from config/r_streams.h (Rprintf, REprintf, Rvprintf,
REvprintf, Rf_error — all stable R API from R_ext/Print.h and
R_ext/Error.h).

This eliminates all symbols that R CMD check flags in compiled code
(stdout, stderr, printf, puts, putchar, vprintf, abort) without
needing the old r_remap.h force-include hack.
